    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An evergreen tree native to southern China, and cultivated elsewhere in southern and eastern Asia. It is prized for its aromatic bark, which is commonly used as the spice cinnamon, though it is not true cinnamon, and as an environmentally-friendly insecticide in the context of conservation.</Note_Text>
